glosses: to claim something as one's own
to stand up for, protect, to defend

examples.text: Biz hiç beceremedik sevmeyi de, terk etmeyi de / Kendimize sahip çıkıp dünyayla yüzleşmeyi de
examples.translation: We could never manage to love or leave each other / To stand up for ourselves and face the world

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish صاحب چیقمق (sahib çıkmak). Morphologically sahip (“owner”) + çıkmak (“to come out, to stand”)
